{"id": 231239186, "title": "North Belfast \"sophisticated cannabis factory\" raided", "text": "Drugs worth an estimated \u00a3600,000 have been seized after a \u201csophisticated cannabis factory\u201d was found in North Belfast, police say. Detectives from the PSNI\u2019s Organised Crime Branch have arrested a man and seized cannabis \u201cwith an estimated street value of more than \u00a3600,000\u201d, they said in a statement issued on Saturday. The statement added: \u201cA sophisticated cannabis factory was uncovered at a commercial warehouse on Limestone Road on Friday 7 June. Follow up enquiries identified a vehicle which was subsequently stopped by police in Holywood. A large quantity of cannabis was located inside the vehicle and the driver, a 32 year old man, was arrested on suspicion of drugs offences. He remains in custody at present.\u201d Read more: Man found with \u201csignificant head injury\u201d leads to attempted murder arrest Read more: Teenager suffers life threatening injuries in two car crash Detective Chief Inspector Mullan said: \u201cAs a Service we are continually working hard to prevent and detect as much drug-related activity as possible and yesterday\u2019s seizure is an example of effective community-based policing at its best. These efforts are in keeping with Operation Dealbreaker, our organisational commitment to tackle every aspect of drug misuse across Northern Ireland, and that includes its harrowing impact on the lives and relationships of local people. There is no such thing as a \u2018safe\u2019 drug.\u201d The DCI added: \u201cInformation from the public is key in helping us to identify the people and places involved in the drugs trade and I would appeal to anyone with any information about suspected drug production or dealing in their area to call the non-emergency number 101 or submit information online via www.psni.police.uk/makeareport.\u201d The police added that people can also share information anonymously with the Crimestoppers charity on 0800 555 111 or online at www.crimestoppers-uk.org. For all the latest news, visit the Belfast Live homepage here and sign up to our daily newsletter here.", "summary": "Limestone Road warehouse raided by Organised Crime Branch officers", "url": "https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/news/belfast-news/north-belfast-sophisticated-cannabis-factory-29317786", "image": "https://i2-prod.belfastlive.co.uk/news/belfast-news/article29317779.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Cannabis-factory-NB2.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 12:42:28", "author": "Maurice Fitzmaurice", "authors": ["Maurice Fitzmaurice"], "language": "en", "source_country": "GB", "sentiment": 0.112}